acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

params.authorizerConfig: The config data for the {Orchestrator_v1}'s {IAuthorizer_v1}                         instance.
params.fundingManagerConfig: The config data for the orchestrator's {IFundingManager_v1}                             instance.
params.moduleConfigs: Variable length set of optional module's config                      data.
params.paymentProcessorConfig: The config data for the orchestrator's                               {IPaymentProcessor_v1} instance.

returns._0: CreatedOrchestrator Returns the created orchestrator instance

deployExternalContract(bytes,bytes[]).details: Any further calls to the contract that serve its initialization         can be provided via the calls array and will be executed after.

params.calls: Additional calls to be made to the deployed contract.
params.code: The creation code of the contract.

returns._0: orchestratorAddress The address of the corresponding {Orchestrator_v1}.
id The id of the next created {Orchestrator_v1}.

params.beacon_: The address of the {IInverterBeacon_v1} containing the {Orchestrator_v1} implementation.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

trustedForwarder().details: Returns the address of the trusted forwarder.

deployExternalContract(bytes,bytes[]).notice: Deploys an external contract using the CREATE2 opcode.

getOrchestratorByID(uint256).notice: Returns the {IOrchestrator_v1} address that corresponds to the given id.

getOrchestratorIDCounter().notice: Returns the counter of the current {Orchestrator_v1} id.
